{"article_id":"biu37I8BaMeV1pd2","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Hillary Clinton testifies for more than five hours before two congressional committees","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"Clinton , at one point , grew exasperated with line of questioning over Benghazi response","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"Some Republican lawmakers say","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"they are not satisfied with Clinton 's answers","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"Four Americans killed in September 11 attack ,","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"including U.S. ambassador to Libya","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"Secretary of State Hillary Clinton on Wednesday took on Republican congressional critics of her department 's handling of the deadly September terrorist attack in Libya .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"Conservative GOP members challenged Clinton on the lack of security at the diplomatic compound in Benghazi as well as the erroneous account","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"that the attack grew spontaneously from a protest over an anti-Islam film","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"produced in the United States .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"At two hearings ,","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"which together totaled more than five hours ,","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"Clinton acknowledged a `` systemic breakdown ''","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"cited by an independent review of issues","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"leading up to the armed assault","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"and said","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"her department was taking additional steps","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"to increase security at U.S. diplomatic facilities .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"Here are five things","depth":4},{"id":20,"text":"we learned from the hearings before the Senate Foreign Relations and House Foreign Affairs committees .","depth":4},{"id":21,"text":"1 . What Clinton did the day of the Benghazi attack","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"Clinton tears up at Benghazi hearing","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"MUST WATCH Clinton tears up at Benghazi hearing 01:16","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"Clinton , senators clash over Benghazi","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"MUST WATCH Clinton , senators clash over Benghazi 04:11","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"JUST WATCHED Clinton 's heated exchange over Benghazi","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"MUST WATCH Clinton 's heated exchange over Benghazi 01:10","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"Clinton spent the better part of last September 11","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"trying to get a handle on security at several other U.S. embassies in the Middle East","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"where anti-American protests were in full swing over an anti-Muslim film","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"produced in the United States .","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"She said","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"the U.S. embassy was `` under assault '' by crowds","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"trying to scale the wall .","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"American embassies in Yemen and Tunisia were also facing a `` serious threat .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"Clinton personally called the president of Tunisia ,","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"she said ,","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"to `` beg him to send reinforcements ,","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"which he did ,","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"to finally save our embassy . ''","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"By 4 p.m. that day , Clinton was notified about the Benghazi attack .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"In the coming hours , she was in meetings","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"and spoke with staff , the American Embassy in Tripoli and other U.S. officials .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"Directing the U.S. response from the State Department ,","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"Clinton stayed in touch with officials across the administration and with the Libyan government .","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"She instructed her staff to `` consider every option ,","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"to just break down the doors of the Libyan officials","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"to get as much security support","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"as we possibly could . ''","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"Clinton said","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"in the hours and days","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"following the attack in Benghazi ,","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"there were `` no delays in decision-making .","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"No denials of support from Washington or from our military , '' something","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"an independent board","depth":14},{"id":61,"text":"established","depth":15},{"id":62,"text":"to review the matter","depth":15},{"id":63,"text":"cited in its report .","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"2 . U.S. diplomatic posts in some 20 countries under threat","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"`` Sitting here today ,","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"we probably have at least 20 other posts","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"that are under a serious threat environment","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"as I speak to you , ''","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"she told senators .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"`` We operate in places","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"where we know","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"that our facilities are being surveilled for potential attacks","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"where we have a steady Intel stream of plotting . ''","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"Clinton detailed what the State Department has done","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"to begin implementing the 29 recommendations of the Accountability Review Board","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"to improve security at diplomatic posts in high-threat areas , in addition to a few of her own .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"Sen. Paul :","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"I would have fired Clinton","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"Sen. Paul :","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"I would have fired Clinton","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"03:10","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"Heated exchanges at Benghazi hearing","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Heated exchanges at Benghazi hearing 04:16","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"Specifically , Clinton has appointed a team ,","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"led by her deputy ,","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"to focus on tightening security ,","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"sent joint teams of military special forces and diplomatic security threat analysts to more than a dozen high-risk posts","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"and appointed a senior official","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"to focus exclusively on those areas .","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"The State Department is also working to streamline requests for security","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"so they make their way more quickly up the chain of leadership .","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"Despite the threat ,","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"Clinton stressed the importance of U.S. leadership and diplomatic presence in the Middle East .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"`` We 've come a long way in the past four years ,","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"and we can not afford to retreat now , ''","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"Clinton told senators .","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"`` When America is absent , especially from unstable environments ,","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"there are consequences .","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"Extremism takes root ,","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"our interests suffer ,","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"our security at home is threatened . ''","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"Clinton grew emotional","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"and held back tears","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"when talking about U.S. personnel","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"killed in the Benghazi attack .","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"`` For me , this is not just a matter of policy ,","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"it 's personal .","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"I stood next to President Obama","depth":15},{"id":115,"text":"as the Marines carried those flag-draped caskets off the plane at Andrews , ''","depth":15},{"id":116,"text":"Clinton said","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"as she choked back tears .","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"`` I put my arms around the mothers and fathers , the sisters and brothers , the sons and daughters , and the wives","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"left alone","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"to raise their children . ''","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"But she lost patience with the focus of Republican senators on talking points","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"used by U.N . Ambassador Susan Rice on the next Sunday 's talk shows","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"that focused on a protest at the U.S. post in Benghazi ,","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"which turned out not to have taken place .","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"When Sen. Ron Johnson pressed Clinton on why the State Department did n't call U.S. personnel","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"who were evacuated from Benghazi","depth":14},{"id":127,"text":"to determine","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"whether there was a protest ,","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"Clinton took him to task .","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"`` With all due respect , the fact is we had four dead Americans , ''","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"Clinton reminded Johnson","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"as she banged her hand on the table .","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"`` Was it because of a protest","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"or was it because of guys","depth":16},{"id":135,"text":"out for a walk one night","depth":16},{"id":136,"text":"decided","depth":16},{"id":137,"text":"they 'd go kill some Americans ?","depth":16},{"id":138,"text":"What difference , at this point , does it make ?","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"It is our job to figure out what happened","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"and do everything","depth":14},{"id":141,"text":"we can","depth":14},{"id":142,"text":"to prevent it from ever happening , ''","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"she said .","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"4 . Militants in Mali and Algeria have arms from Libya","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"Clinton warned","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"the security situation in northern Mali ,","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"where international forces are battling militants ,","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"has been exacerbated by flow of weapons from neighboring Libya","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"following the fall of Moammar Gadhafi .","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"She said","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"there was `` no doubt ''","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"such weapons were also used in an attack by militants on an Algerian natural gas plant last week .","depth":13},{"id":153,"text":"She noted","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"the aftermath of the Arab spring has changed power dynamics","depth":14},{"id":155,"text":"and stretched security forces across the region thin .","depth":14},{"id":156,"text":"Calling the campaign struggle against the Islamic fighters a necessary response to `` a very serious , ongoing threat , ''","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"Clinton said","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"the `` United States can not permit northern Mali to become a safe-haven for Islamist rebels","depth":14},{"id":159,"text":"that could eventually pose a more direct threat to U.S . interests . ''","depth":14},{"id":160,"text":"Noting the increased strength of al Qaeda in the Islamic Maghreb , the regional affiliate of the al Qaeda network","depth":15},{"id":161,"text":"fighting along side local Malians ,","depth":15},{"id":162,"text":"Clinton warned","depth":14},{"id":163,"text":"that the United States must prepare for the possibility","depth":16},{"id":164,"text":"that groups like AQIM could threaten direct attacks on U.S. interests","depth":17},{"id":165,"text":"as they gain power . `` You ca n't say","depth":17},{"id":166,"text":"because they have n't done something","depth":16},{"id":167,"text":"they 're not going to do it , ''","depth":16},{"id":168,"text":"Clinton said .","depth":14},{"id":169,"text":"`` This is not only a terrorist syndicate ,","depth":15},{"id":170,"text":"it is a criminal enterprise .","depth":15},{"id":171,"text":"So make no mistake about it ,","depth":14},{"id":172,"text":"we 've got to have a better strategy . ''","depth":13},{"id":173,"text":"While their tone was generally respectful ,","depth":11},{"id":174,"text":"several Republican senators made clear","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"they were unsatisfied with Clinton 's answers .","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"Sen. John McCain , R-Arizona , one of the administration 's toughest critics since the Benghazi attack , took Clinton to task for what he considered lackluster attention to the growing threat in Benghazi .","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"McCain wanted to know","depth":14},{"id":178,"text":"why Clinton had n't read a cable from Ambassador Christopher Stevens","depth":15},{"id":179,"text":"warning","depth":16},{"id":180,"text":"that the mission in Benghazi could not survive a sustained assault .","depth":16},{"id":181,"text":"Sen. Rand Paul said","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"it would have been an offense worthy of firing Clinton","depth":14},{"id":183,"text":"had he been president .","depth":14},{"id":184,"text":"McCain also blasted Clinton 's answers to questions about the administration 's claim","depth":13},{"id":185,"text":"that a protest had taken place in Benghazi .","depth":13},{"id":186,"text":"`` The American people deserve to know answers ,","depth":14},{"id":187,"text":"and they certainly do n't deserve false answers , ''","depth":14},{"id":188,"text":"McCain told Clinton .","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"Clinton was more diplomatic with her old friend ,","depth":11},{"id":190,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"she respected his strong feelings for the incident","depth":14},{"id":192,"text":"given his own relationship with Stevens ,","depth":14},{"id":193,"text":"but that they disagreed about what happened and when it happened","depth":14},{"id":194,"text":"with respect to explaining events .","depth":14},{"id":195,"text":"In addition to lessons","depth":15},{"id":196,"text":"the State Department learned","depth":15},{"id":197,"text":"about improving security at diplomatic posts ,","depth":14},{"id":198,"text":"Clinton ,","depth":15},{"id":199,"text":"who called the Benghazi attack an act of terrorism since Day One ,","depth":15},{"id":200,"text":"suggested","depth":14},{"id":201,"text":"the administration might learn another lesson .","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"`` Just withhold .","depth":12},{"id":203,"text":"Do n't say what you do n't know for sure","depth":13},{"id":204,"text":"until it 's finally decided . ''","depth":13}],"relations":[{"parent":409,"left":0,"right":408,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":408,"left":222,"right":407,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":222,"left":208,"right":221,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":208,"left":206,"right":207,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":206,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":207,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":221,"left":209,"right":220,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":209,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":220,"left":212,"right":219,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":212,"left":7,"right":211,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":211,"left":8,"right":210,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration"